node.text:
A firefighter watches wildfires blaze near the village of Kuel in Yakutia, Sakha, Russia, on Sunday, Aug. 8, 2021. 

The wildfires raging across Siberia are now so massive, they’re bigger than all the other large wildfires across the globe put together.

The fires have burned about 62,000 square miles. That's about the size of Florida. 

Click the link in our bio to learn more. 

📸: Ivan Nikiforov/Anadolu Agency via Getty Images

#Wildfires #Russia #Siberia #ClimateChange

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by The Weather Channel on August 11, 2021. May be an image of road.

node.text:
The local trade association estimates that more than 400,000 vehicles suffered water damage in last month's flood in Zhengzhou, China.

Photos show one of the lots where damaged cars have been towed. Row after row of cars, many of which will need to be discarded entirely, sit to wait out their fate.

On July 20, the already waterlogged Zhengzhou was inundated with 8 inches of rain in just one hour. The rapid rainfall turned roads into rivers, washing away hundreds of thousands of vehicles, trapping children in schools, and stranding workers overnight in their workplaces. Earlier this month, according to the Henan provincial government, the flood's death toll reached 302. The majority of the victims were in Zhengzhou.

Click the link in our bio to see more photos of the fields of damaged cars in Zhengzhou.

Photo by Feature China/Barcroft Media via Getty Images

#ZhengzhouFlood #ChinaFlood #SevereWeather

node.text:
The Perseids, the best meteor shower of the year, peaks this week.

You can expect to see up to 60 meteors an hour. The moon will only be 13% full, so it should be quite the show.

Click the link in our bio to find out when you can catch it.

📸 : Gabriel Gonzalez/Getty Images

#Perseid #MeteorShower #SkyWatching #NightSky

The storm is approaching the Dominican Republic. Areas along its path can expect heavy rain and gusty winds in the coming days.

Florida remains in the cone of this tropical storm, but it faces an uncertain future filled with land interaction, dry air and wind shear.
